Acme-Be-Modern

This is a source filter that enables you to write 'be modern' instead
of 'use Modern::Perl'. In other words you can replace one line (17
characters) with two lines (31 characters), and at the same time make
you program less stable. All this for free!

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Acme::Be::Modern

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Acme-Be-Modern

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Acme-Be-Modern

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Acme-Be-Modern

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Acme-Be-Modern/


